#. [unit_type], id=Goblin Ravager LotI, race=monster
#: .\units\Goblin_Ravager.cfg:18
msgid ""
"To perform their destructive work effectively, Goblin Pillagers must be able "
"to move fast. In the event of a shortage of wolves, another mount has to fill"
" in. Though giant spiders are far less intelligent than wolves, the fear "
"spread by their sight makes up for this imperfection. Taming those beasts "
"claims high casualties and their appetite for riders in front of them is "
"detrimental – but one has to overlook such little mishaps leniently: Goblins "
"are numerous, useless for most other jobs, and since birth used to submit to "
"their fates."
