msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Lich King LotI, race=undead
#: .\units\Lich_King.cfg:4
msgid "Lich King"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Lich King LotI, race=undead
#: .\units\Lich_King.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Lich Kings are powerful undead warriors with free will and magic powers. "
"Unlike other undead, they are not obeying a master, they are raising and "
"controlling their minions, and unlike liches, they are leading their minions "
"into battles."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Lunatic Knight LotI, race=human
#: .\units\Lunatic_Knight.cfg:4
msgid "Lunatic Knight"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Lunatic Knight LotI, race=human
#: .\units\Lunatic_Knight.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Lunatic knights are ones of the most zealous warriors a warlord might employ."
" The reason why they fight is neither glory nor gold. They enjoy the thrill "
"of battles, and that motivates them to join armed conflicts. In battle, they "
"are feared adversaries, their fervour, speed and strength are a huge threat "
"for anyone. They usually die before they realise that Lunatic Knights are not"
" quite well protected, and can fall whenever their charge fails to defeat "
"their target."
msgstr ""

#. [advancement], id=penetrate2
