msgid "Sword Mage"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Sword Mage LotI, race=human
#: .\units\Sword_Mage.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Because both mages and fencers prefer not to use armours, some mages or "
"fencers came to an idea to practise both with a sword and with spells. This "
"is incredibly hard to learn, requiring them to study in libraries and "
"practise sword fights with any fighter who happens to cross their way, such "
"as silk-stocking duelists wandering around, itching after potential affronts."
" No matter if they are mages or fencers, they are always considered to be too"
" different by their fellow mages or fencers, and are excluded. As a result, "
"they dislike the society and argue with any possible comrade. Due to this, "
"all allies adjacent to a Sword Mage do 20% less damage."
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\Sword_Mage.cfg:130
msgid "female^Sword Mage"
msgstr ""

#. [advancement], id=arcane_penetrate2
