#. [unit_type], id=09 Great Mage
#: .\units\enemies\09_Great_Mage.cfg:9
msgid ""
"In the past, any person who was even considered for the title of Great Mage "
"was quite nearly a legend in their own time, and town criers had forcibly "
"learnt discretion in applying the title. Merit for the title is carefully "
"considered by a council of the leading magi of the age, and the conferment of"
" the title was given only by a majority vote. Regardless, anyone who was "
"seriously nominated for the honor of being called a Great Mage was, without "
"question, a master of their art, and had surpassed almost any of their peers "
"in skill.\n"
"\n"
"In present, Wesnothian mages grew much more powerful, and reaching the level "
"of Great Mage is quite common. Because their art progressed so far, the sheer"
" fear of their spells keeps many lands in obedience.\n"
"\n"
"Though they are not warriors, by any means, the application of their art to "
"combat is something that often causes other soldiers to stand aside in awe."
msgstr ""

