#. [race], id=black soul-loti
#: .\units\enemies\black_soul_race.cfg:4
msgid "race^Black Soul"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=black soul-loti
#: .\units\enemies\black_soul_race.cfg:5
msgid "race^Black Souls"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=black soul-loti
#: .\units\enemies\black_soul_race.cfg:7
msgid ""
"Black Souls are not summoned or commanded by a necromancer. They are spirits "
"of those who passed away and do NOT rest in peace but refuse the natural "
"order. Filled with hatred, they try to force return into earthly existence. "
"As long as they are locked in the world of the dead, they pose little thread "
"to the living. But if they find a way to break out, they spread their evil "
"among them – the consequences are most often terrible.\n"
"\n"
"Incredibly strong and persistent, not hesitating to unite with demons or "
"other monstrosities, they are horrible opponents under any circumstances."
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=burning soul-loti
#: .\units\enemies\burning_soul_race.cfg:4
msgid "race^Burning Soul"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=burning soul-loti
#: .\units\enemies\burning_soul_race.cfg:5
msgid "race^Burning Souls"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=burning soul-loti
#: .\units\enemies\burning_soul_race.cfg:7
msgid ""
"Burning Souls are the tormented spirits of people slain by demons or "
"otherwise dragged into Inferno. With their free will suppressed by insanity, "
"there is no more left than pain and sorrow. They suffer hell, Uria's demons "
"burn them alive, both out- and inwardly, but have them regenerate instantly "
"to survive forever. The tormentors control bodies and limbs, cause these poor"
" souls to even hurt themselves and increase the agony (if such is possible at"
" all) or set them against enemies of their demonic queen.\n"
"\n"
"Ultimately, Burning Souls seek nothing but their own death, because only "
"death can free them from their suffering. Outside help, which would – given a"
" vestige of sound mind and enough mental strength remained – eventually allow"
" them to escape from this cruel, never-ending cycle almost never comes."
msgstr ""

