#. [unit_type], id=Demon Infiltrator Mage of Light, race=demon-loti
#: .\units\enemies\demon_infiltrators.cfg:485
msgid ""
"After years of experience, the most devout of white magi develop vast "
"spiritual powers. By strict devotion to the path of the light, they can call "
"upon its aid to chase away the shadows of the night.\n"
"\n"
"Following a strict code of piety and honor, these men and women work "
"tirelessly to bring life and order to the troubled world in which they live, "
"though this one seems to be an exception."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Demon Infiltrator Messenger, race=demon-loti
#: .\units\enemies\demon_infiltrators.cfg:868
msgid ""
"This is another foul demon pretending to be a human, and a bringer of good "
"and light. They usually assist false Prophets"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Demon Infiltrator Prophet, race=demon-loti
#: .\units\enemies\demon_infiltrators.cfg:1336
msgid "This is surely a false prophet, an excellent manipulator."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Demon Infiltrator Shock Trooper, race=demon-loti
#: .\units\enemies\demon_infiltrators.cfg:2319
msgid ""
"The sight of Demonic Shock Troopers breaking an enemy often does the same to "
"the morale of any opposition, who sometimes wonder if such armour covers "
"monsters, rather than men. And really, most of them don't even look like men,"
" they are using heavy armours to hide their demonic appearance"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Demon Infiltrator Iron Mauler, race=demon-loti
#: .\units\enemies\demon_infiltrators.cfg:2406
msgid ""
"Only exceptionally strong demons disguise themselves as Iron Maulers, but "
"meeting one usually means doom."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Demon Infiltrator Destroyer LotI, race=demon-loti
#: .\units\enemies\demon_infiltrators.cfg:2478
msgid ""
"Destroyers are the strongest of demons that managed to disguise as humans. It"
" is strongly recommended to stay far away from them, if you manage to "
"identify them."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Demon Infiltrator Fencer, race=demon-loti
#: .\units\enemies\demon_infiltrators.cfg:2566
msgid ""
"Fencers belong to a school of thought that considers the armor most soldiers "
"wear in combat to be their own worst enemy. While armor can only soften a "
"blow, evading it leaves the defender completely unharmed. Being able to "
"reliably dodge any offensive move is a luxury only afforded to the fit of "
"body, and then only to those who endure rigorous training.\n"
"\n"
"Outfitted with only a dagger and saber, fencers are light on their feet and "
"useful in many situations where their armor-bound peers are at a "
"disadvantage. They relish dancing circles around troops like heavy infantry, "
"mocking the weight of their full armor."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Demon Infiltrator Thug, race=demon-loti
#: .\units\enemies\demon_infiltrators.cfg:3206
msgid "Some demons chose to disguise themselves as criminals, who knows why."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Demon Infiltrator Bandit, race=demon-loti
#: .\units\enemies\demon_infiltrators.cfg:3301
msgid ""
"Some demons chose to disguise themselves as those excluded from the human "
"society, who knows why."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Demon Infiltrator Highwayman, race=demon-loti
#: .\units\enemies\demon_infiltrators.cfg:3397
msgid ""
"Highwaymen have gained an infamous reputation for underhanded deeds of "
"violence. Demonic Highwaymen have hyperbolised this reputation even more."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Demon Infiltrator Footpad, race=demon-loti
#: .\units\enemies\demon_infiltrators.cfg:3489
msgid ""
"These weaker demons are often derisively called ‘footpads’ by their "
"superiors, for they are tasked with any job that requires a great deal of "
"running around, often being employed as couriers, or scouts. Their superiors "
"often do this just to have fun from seeing their faces after telling them how"
" far will they have to go."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=impact, range=melee
#: .\units\enemies\demon_infiltrators.cfg:3506
msgid "club"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Demon Infiltrator Outlaw, race=demon-loti
#: .\units\enemies\demon_infiltrators.cfg:3692
msgid ""
"Some demonic infiltrators were really angered by the difficulty of making "
"arrows, so they prefer using slings to shoot rocks they can find anywhere."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Demon Infiltrator Fugitive, race=demon-loti
#: .\units\enemies\demon_infiltrators.cfg:3879
msgid ""
"These demons can hide in villages, saying that it is their stealth skill, but"
" in truth it is simply that nobody dares to report that they are in their "
"village."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Demon Infiltrator Poacher, race=demon-loti
#: .\units\enemies\demon_infiltrators.cfg:4065
msgid ""
"Some demons chose to disguise as archers, and it is not very known why they "
"don't use their fireballs instead. Probably to make an army of demonic "
"infiltrators look more realistic."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Demon Infiltrator Trapper, race=demon-loti
#: .\units\enemies\demon_infiltrators.cfg:4193
msgid ""
"Some demons started to understand the nature of forests, but they are not "
"used to it as much as elves are."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#: .\units\enemies\demon_infiltrators_unidentified.cfg:834
msgid "sword"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Bewitched Wolf, race=wolf
#: .\units\enemies\demon_infiltrators_unidentified.cfg:908
msgid "Bewitched Wolf"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Bewitched Wolf, race=wolf
#: .\units\enemies\demon_infiltrators_unidentified.cfg:922
msgid "This wolf is controlled by a strong spell, making it obey its caster."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Demon Lord, race=demon lord-loti
#. [female]
#: .\units\enemies\Demon_Lord.cfg:4
#: .\units\enemies\Demon_Lord.cfg:176
msgid "Demon Lord"
msgstr ""

#. [trait], id=disastrous
#: .\units\enemies\Demon_Lord.cfg:40
msgid "disastrous"
msgstr ""

#. [trait], id=disastrous
#: .\units\enemies\Demon_Lord.cfg:41
msgid "female^disastrous"
msgstr ""

#. [trait], id=disastrous
#: .\units\enemies\Demon_Lord.cfg:42
msgid "cleaves"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Demon Manowar, race=demon-loti
#: .\units\enemies\Demon_Manowar.cfg:4
msgid "Demon Man o'War"
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\enemies\Demon_Manowar.cfg:212
msgid "Demoness Man o'War"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Demon Overlord, race=demon-loti
#: .\units\enemies\Demon_Overlord.cfg:4
msgid "Demon Overlord"
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\enemies\Demon_Overlord.cfg:211
msgid "Demoness Overlord"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Demon Soul, race=undead
#: .\units\enemies\Demon_Soul.cfg:5
#: .\units\enemies\Demon_Soul.cfg:161
msgid "Demon Soul"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Demon Soul, race=undead
#: .\units\enemies\Demon_Soul.cfg:22
#: .\units\enemies\Demon_Soul.cfg:178
msgid ""
"Worship of dark deities can bind a demon in his revered place of rest and "
"force him to guard it. These undead demons are restless, unable to get too "
"far from their grave, but no adventurer who ever visits Inferno is strongly "
"advised not to approach these places."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Demon Warrior, race=demon-loti
#: .\units\enemies\Demon_Warrior.cfg:4
msgid "Demon Warrior"
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\enemies\Demon_Warrior.cfg:216
msgid "Demoness Warrior"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Doom Imp, race=imp-loti
#: .\units\enemies\Doom_Imp.cfg:4
msgid "Doom Imp"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Doom Imp, race=imp-loti
#: .\units\enemies\Doom_Imp.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Doom imps is an improved variation of imps, that can be also usable in times "
"of war as meatshields."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Dracolich, race=undead
#: .\units\enemies\Dracolich.cfg:4
msgid "Dracolich"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Dracolich, race=undead
#: .\units\enemies\Dracolich.cfg:32
msgid ""
"The most evil and twisted dragons explore the dark side of the magic, just "
"like the necromancers. Upon death or when they decide, they become "
"dracoliches, terrible abominations far stronger than dragons, far stronger "
"than liches, far stronger than anything in this world."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Faerie Fire Unit, race=monster
#: .\units\enemies\Faerie_fire_unit.cfg:5
msgid "Faerie Fire"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Faerie Fire Unit, race=monster
#: .\units\enemies\Faerie_fire_unit.cfg:20
msgid ""
"This is a piece of faerie fire that can exist without external source of "
"magical power. It is not too powerful, although it can incinerate foes and "
"thereby create other separate faerie fires."
msgstr ""

#. [specials]
#: .\units\enemies\Faerie_fire_unit.cfg:101
msgid "Faerie Fire Unit"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Fire Reaper, race=monster
#: .\units\enemies\Fire_Reaper.cfg:4
msgid "Fire Reaper"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Flies, race=monster
#: .\units\enemies\Flies.cfg:4
msgid "Flies"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Flies, race=monster
#: .\units\enemies\Flies.cfg:17
msgid ""
"A fly, even if it is a bloodsucking horse-fly, is completely harmless, but a "
"swarm of them can be a threat. They drink only a drop of blood with each "
"bite, but if they are numerous enough, it can add up to fatal blood loss."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Flower of Evil, race=monster
#: .\units\enemies\Flower_of_Evil.cfg:4
msgid "Flower of Evil"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Flower of Evil, race=monster
#: .\units\enemies\Flower_of_Evil.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Flowers of Evil are one of the few plant types adopted to the hostile "
"environment in Inferno after Uria's arrival. They are dangerous even to "
"approach, and their main source of food are creatures living around, imps and"
" demons, but if more interesting prey is nearby, they leave them alone. They "
"are extremely dangerous in proximity of symbiotic mushrooms."
msgstr ""

#. [chance_to_hit], id=marksman
#: .\units\enemies\Flower_of_Evil.cfg:78
msgid "assisted marksman"
msgstr ""

#. [chance_to_hit], id=marksman
#: .\units\enemies\Flower_of_Evil.cfg:79
msgid ""
"When used offensively, this attack always has at least a 60% chance to hit if"
" any allied Deathshrooms or Hatredshrooms are near this unit."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Fog, race=undead
#: .\units\enemies\Fog.cfg:56
msgid ""
"Fog is a materialised concentration of magical energy that can exist without "
"a constant magic source. The offensive magic cast upon it has nearly no "
"effect, because it heals from that source of magic as fast as it is hurt by "
"it. But a bladed weapon can shred its ethereal body into pieces easily."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=fire, range=ranged
#: .\units\enemies\Fog.cfg:143
msgid "horrible lightning"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=half god_loti
#: .\units\enemies\half_god_race.cfg:4
msgid "race^Half-god"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=half god_loti
#: .\units\enemies\half_god_race.cfg:5
msgid "race^Half-gods"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=half god_loti
#: .\units\enemies\half_god_race.cfg:7
msgid ""
"A half god is a creature that is partially a god and partially a human being,"
" they are usually created when a mortal is worshipped like a god or as direct"
" offspring of beings touched by divine power."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Hatredshroom, race=monster
#: .\units\enemies\Hatredshroom.cfg:4
msgid "Hatredshroom"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Hatredshroom, race=monster
#: .\units\enemies\Hatredshroom.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Hatredshroom is a venomous mushroom that grows in symbiosis with Flowers of "
"Evil. It feeds on the very essence of hatred that exists around it, and "
"channels it to nearby infernal plants, that give it substances it needs to "
"grow."
msgstr ""

#. [regenerate], id=symbiosis 36
#: .\units\enemies\Hatredshroom.cfg:25
msgid "symbiosis (36)"
msgstr ""

#. [regenerate], id=symbiosis 36
#: .\units\enemies\Hatredshroom.cfg:26
msgid "female^symbiosis (36)"
msgstr ""

#. [regenerate], id=symbiosis 36
#: .\units\enemies\Hatredshroom.cfg:27
msgid ""
"The unit will heal itself 36 HP per turn, if there is a Flower of Evil or "
"Voracius Herb next to it. If it is poisoned, it will remove the poison "
"instead of healing."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Hellhound, race=monster
#: .\units\enemies\Hellhound.cfg:4
msgid "Hellhound"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Hellhound, race=monster
#: .\units\enemies\Hellhound.cfg:20
msgid ""
"Hellhounds fearsome monsters that live in Inferno. They are used by demons as"
" guardians or cheaper attack force. Their mighty jaws can crush most enemies,"
" and their fiery breath can kill a lot of victims as well."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=fire, range=ranged
#: .\units\enemies\Hellhound.cfg:40
msgid "fire breath"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Spearman_steel
#: .\units\enemies\hybrids_of_steel.cfg:35
msgid "Malefactor"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Spearman_steel
#: .\units\enemies\hybrids_of_steel.cfg:48
msgid ""
"Many people were offered to join the Steel Future army, with promises of "
"ruling the world and a great improvement of their bodies. Most of them agreed"
" and large robotic objects were inserted into their bodies, whose control "
"might be quite hard, but grants incredible strength and resilience. They are "
"the main components of an army that is supposed to conquer the world after "
"the Great Disaster."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Javelineer_steel
#: .\units\enemies\hybrids_of_steel.cfg:78
msgid "Scoundrel"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Javelineer_steel
#: .\units\enemies\hybrids_of_steel.cfg:95
msgid ""
"Some spearmen of the Steel Future Army did surprisingly decide that spear is "
"their weapon of choice, becoming quite dangerous even with spears."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Swordsman_steel
#: .\units\enemies\hybrids_of_steel.cfg:127
msgid "Knave"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Swordsman_steel
#: .\units\enemies\hybrids_of_steel.cfg:144
msgid ""
"As the new soldiers who chose to use mechanical components in their bodies "
"grow in experience, they may come to command their iron limbs better, and "
"thereby gain proficiency at using swords."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Royal Guard_steel, race=human
#: .\units\enemies\hybrids_of_steel.cfg:165
msgid "Steel Scourge"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Royal Guard_steel, race=human
#: .\units\enemies\hybrids_of_steel.cfg:187
msgid ""
"Once the soldiers come to master the control of their mechanical limbs, they "
"become real monsters nobody wants to see."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Lieutenant_steel
#: .\units\enemies\hybrids_of_steel.cfg:368
msgid "Enfant Terrible"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Lieutenant_steel
#: .\units\enemies\hybrids_of_steel.cfg:385
msgid ""
"Members of the army of the Steel Future conspiracy may possess some knowledge"
" of warfare, and if they do, they are asked to lead divisions."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=General_steel
#: .\units\enemies\hybrids_of_steel.cfg:413
msgid "Offender"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=General_steel
#: .\units\enemies\hybrids_of_steel.cfg:430
msgid ""
"The most wicked of the members of the army of Steel Future will be granted "
"this rank, the rank of a knight with terrible cunning, probably because he is"
" using a mechanical calculator."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Grand Marshal_steel, race=human
#: .\units\enemies\hybrids_of_steel.cfg:459
msgid "Antihero"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Grand Marshal_steel, race=human
#: .\units\enemies\hybrids_of_steel.cfg:488
msgid "These are the leaders of the Steel Future society."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Dark Adept_steel, race=human
#: .\units\enemies\hybrids_of_steel.cfg:770
msgid "Brat"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Dark Adept_steel, race=human
#: .\units\enemies\hybrids_of_steel.cfg:797
msgid ""
"These guys are those who chose to walk the same path as Akula. If you won't "
"interrupt their studies, they will become really great freaks very soon."
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\enemies\hybrids_of_steel.cfg:988
msgid "female^Brat"
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\enemies\hybrids_of_steel.cfg:992
msgid ""
"These gals are those who chose to walk the same path as Akula. If you won't "
"interrupt their studies, they will become really great freaks very soon."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Dark Sorcerer_steel, race=human
#: .\units\enemies\hybrids_of_steel.cfg:1064
msgid "Villain"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Dark Sorcerer_steel, race=human
#: .\units\enemies\hybrids_of_steel.cfg:1086
msgid ""
"Already close to reaching the level of power required to become a superior "
"spellcaster, they should be slain before they finish their preparation."
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\enemies\hybrids_of_steel.cfg:1261
msgid "female^Villain"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Necromancer_steel, race=human
#: .\units\enemies\hybrids_of_steel.cfg:1360
msgid "Reprobate"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Necromancer_steel, race=human
#: .\units\enemies\hybrids_of_steel.cfg:1383
msgid ""
"Having acquired terrible powers using the powers granted by ancient "
"technologies, this kind of necromancers is really a terrible thing to see. "
"Unlike other greater soldiers of the Steel Future, they chose to strengthen "
"their spellcasting ability instead of punishing melee attackers with swarming"
" tentacles."
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\enemies\hybrids_of_steel.cfg:1621
msgid "female^Reprobate"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Lich_steel, race=monster
#: .\units\enemies\hybrids_of_steel.cfg:1759
msgid "Leech"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Lich_steel, race=monster
#: .\units\enemies\hybrids_of_steel.cfg:1769
msgid ""
"A lich is the physical embodiment of black magic’s first goal: the quest to "
"achieve immortality. Though a great deal is sacrificed in the rebirth, in "
"becoming a lich one cheats death of that which truly gives it terror. For it "
"is the mind that is retained, and the spirit which follows, though the body "
"may wither away.  When that necromancer's body is already mechanical, the "
"result is a truly terrifying blend of the worst of man and machine."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Bowman_steel
#: .\units\enemies\hybrids_of_steel.cfg:1850
msgid "Miscreant"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Bowman_steel
#: .\units\enemies\hybrids_of_steel.cfg:1867
msgid "These are former woodsmen, who are now members of the Steel Future Army."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Longbowman_steel
#: .\units\enemies\hybrids_of_steel.cfg:1893
msgid "Crook"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Longbowman_steel
#: .\units\enemies\hybrids_of_steel.cfg:1910
msgid ""
"Thanks to robotic parts implanted into their bodies, these soldiers can shoot"
" from their bows with an incredible speed."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Fencer_steel
#: .\units\enemies\hybrids_of_steel.cfg:1939
msgid "Culprit"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Fencer_steel
#: .\units\enemies\hybrids_of_steel.cfg:1956
msgid ""
"The wiser of those whose bodies were improved with implants chose to fight "
"carefully, focusing at blocking attacks instead of simply enduring them."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Duelist_steel
#: .\units\enemies\hybrids_of_steel.cfg:1975
msgid "Felon"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Duelist_steel
#: .\units\enemies\hybrids_of_steel.cfg:1992
msgid ""
"Some of the Steel Future soldiers developed their combat abilities so high "
"that their overconfidence makes them occasionally even challenge other "
"soldiers into a duel to death, just to be known as a strong fighter."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Heimdall
#: .\units\enemies\hybrids_of_steel.cfg:2026
msgid "Bifröst Guardian"
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=arcane, range=ranged
#: .\units\enemies\hybrids_of_steel.cfg:2325
msgid "Gjallarhorn"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Dragon, race=monster
#: .\units\enemies\Ice_Dragon.cfg:4
msgid "Ice Dragon"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Dragon, race=monster
#: .\units\enemies\Ice_Dragon.cfg:30
msgid ""
"An ice dragon is a legendary creature, normally seen only in fantastic tales."
" They are very rare, and were it not for the historical events, the "
"singlehanded destruction of cities and towns that these creatures have "
"wrought, they might be dismissed as mere myth. Legends are very specific "
"about the ravages of ice dragons; noting their great strength, speed, their "
"preternatural cunning, and above all else, the great cold that accumulates "
"inside of them all the time.\n"
"\n"
"Battling a dragon is said to be the pinnacle of danger itself, fit only for "
"fools, or the bravest of knights."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=cold, range=ranged
#. [effect], apply_to=new_attack, type=cold, range=ranged
#: .\units\enemies\Ice_Dragon.cfg:63
#: .\utils\amla.cfg:2459
msgid "icy breath"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Spirit, race=monster
#: .\units\enemies\Ice_Spirit.cfg:4
msgid "Ice Spirit"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Spirit, race=monster
#: .\units\enemies\Ice_Spirit.cfg:33
msgid ""
"Ice Spirits unearthly apparitions of liquid gases. No one is exactly sure "
"where they come from, but they are occasionally summoned by powerful mages to"
" do their bidding. When not being controlled they like to wander iced plains "
"and take great delight in freezing anything they can reach."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#: .\units\enemies\Ice_Spirit.cfg:36
#: .\units\enemies\Ice_Wraith.cfg:62
msgid "icy claws"
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=cold, range=ranged
#: .\units\enemies\Ice_Spirit.cfg:45
#: .\units\enemies\Ice_Wraith.cfg:71
msgid "freezing breath"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Wraith, race=monster
#: .\units\enemies\Ice_Wraith.cfg:4
msgid "Ice Wraith"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Wraith, race=monster
#: .\units\enemies\Ice_Wraith.cfg:59
msgid ""
"Ice Wraiths are spirits from the coldest places in the world. No one is "
"exactly sure where they come from, but they are occasionally summoned by "
"powerful mages to do their bidding. The odd armor they wear hints at a former"
" life or creator, but whatever ancient civilization was involved has been "
"lost to history and climate change."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Imp, race=imp-loti
#: .\units\enemies\Imp.cfg:4
msgid "Imp"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Imp, race=imp-loti
#: .\units\enemies\Imp.cfg:16
msgid ""
"Imps are foul creations of demons to do the inferior work for the demons, "
"like cleaning dens. Imps are weaker than demons and almost mindless."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Incendiary Drone, race=monster
#: .\units\enemies\Incendiary_Drone.cfg:4
msgid "Incendiary Drone"
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=fire, range=melee
#: .\units\enemies\Incendiary_Drone.cfg:43
msgid "flame"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Merchant, race=human
#: .\units\enemies\Merchant.cfg:4
msgid "Merchant"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Merchant, race=human
#: .\units\enemies\Merchant.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Merchants are masters of buying items from people who do not need them, "
"transport them to another location and sell them to people who need them and "
"are willing to pay more. Those who have unneeded items are happy to get money"
" from them, those who need items are happy to buy them, so everybody likes "
"merchants."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=impact, range=ranged
#: .\units\enemies\Merchant.cfg:22
msgid "cargo throw"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Meteor, race=mechanical
#: .\units\enemies\Meteor.cfg:4
msgid "Meteor"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Meteor, race=mechanical
#: .\units\enemies\Meteor.cfg:16
msgid ""
"Meteoroids are huge rocks falling from the sky, destroying anything they fall"
" on. The fires they are wrapped in as they fly through the air are called "
"meteor. They usually come also with a huge shockwave that can be more "
"damaging than the fire."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Mist, race=undead
#: .\units\enemies\Mist.cfg:41
msgid "Mist"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Mist, race=undead
#: .\units\enemies\Mist.cfg:55
msgid ""
"Mist is a materialised concentration of magical energy that can exist without"
" a constant magic source. The offensive magic cast upon it has nearly no "
"effect, because it heals from that source of magic as fast as it is hurt by "
"it. But a bladed weapon can shred its ethereal body into pieces easily. It "
"can be sometimes dangerous for its lightning bolts."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Phantom of the Opera
#: .\units\enemies\Phantom_of_the_Opera.cfg:4
msgid "Phantom of the Opera"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Phoenix, race=monster
#. [unit_type], id=Solid Phoenix, race=monster
#: .\units\enemies\Phoenix.cfg:4
#: .\units\enemies\Phoenix.cfg:168
msgid "Phoenix"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Phoenix, race=monster
#: .\units\enemies\Phoenix.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Phoenixes are fiery birds from other worlds. They are almost immortal, and "
"also terribly powerful. However, it is supposed that killing one may "
"resurrect also the dead."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Solid Phoenix, race=monster
#: .\units\enemies\Phoenix.cfg:183
msgid ""
"When the phoenix was moved into Chillhold, its lava-hot fire solidified into "
"a stone crust that is uneasy to break for anything. But it is almost unable "
"to move, so it is not very likely to cause severe wounds to anybody."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Powerslave
#: .\units\enemies\Powerslave.cfg:4
msgid "Powerslave"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Power Generator, race=monster
#: .\units\enemies\Power_Generator.cfg:5
msgid "Power Generator"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Power Generator, race=monster
#: .\units\enemies\Power_Generator.cfg:34
msgid ""
"High amounts of an unknown kind energy are created in this machine, and used "
"in an unknown way somewhere else. You have pretty much no idea what this "
"thing is meant to do. The light it creates seems to harm everyone nearby."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Machine Fabricator
#: .\units\enemies\Power_Generator.cfg:254
msgid "Machine Fabricator"
